query:
create table if not exists registrations (
            user_id bigint unsigned not null primary key,
            status enum(
                "UNREGISTERED",
                "STARTED",
                "NAME_ENTERED",
                "KIND_FOUND",
                "VERIFIED",
                "PRONOUNS_PICKED",
                "REGISTERED",
                "FAILED"
            ) not null default "UNREGISTERED",
            name varchar(1024) null,
            kind enum(
                "UNDERGRAD",
                "POSTGRAD",
                "MENTOR",
                "SENIOR_MENTOR",
                "HONORARY_MENTOR",
                "FACULTY"
            ) null
        )
